Deep Green Resistance (DGR) is a radical environmental feminist movement that views mainstream environmental activism as being largely ineffective. "Deep Green Resistance / DGR" is also used by group members to refer to their particular political strategies. The group believes that industrial civilization, as they define it, is endangering all life on the planet, and that a broad range of tactics are needed to achieve environmental and social justice. They argue for a radical shift in societal structures and functions.
